commitResults.messageTitle: GUI: Implement JavaFX interface with formal theme
commitResults.messageBody:
Replace the CLI loop with a JavaFX graphical interface using FXML.
Add a Launcher class to resolve runtime issues with Azul JDK 17 on
macOS. Apply a dark mode CSS theme to match the formal 'Gojo'
persona and update dialog strings to be more authoritative.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor: Apply varargs to Parser methods
commitResults.messageBody:
Update method signatures to accept variable arguments. This removes
unnecessary array creation and streamlines command processing logic.

GUI upgrades and minor bug fixes
Refactor: Add assertions to validate internal state
commitResults.messageBody:
Introduce Java assertions to verify assumptions about method arguments
and class invariants. This improves the defensiveness of the code and
helps catch logical errors early during runtime execution.

commitResults.messageTitle: refactor: improve code quality using SLAP Refactor core logic to adhere to coding standards and improve overall maintainability. This addresses issues regarding abstraction levels, naming conventions, and hardcoded values.
commitResults.messageBody:
- Apply Single Level of Abstraction Principle (SLAP) to long methods
- Extract magic literals and command strings into named constants
- Rename variables to be more descriptive and meaningful
- Remove deep nesting by using guard clauses where appropriate

commitResults.messageTitle: Improve formatting of add task response message
commitResults.messageBody:
- Fix Checkstyle violations caused by long string concatenation lines
- Wrap string literals and concatenations to comply with line length rules
- Improve readability and maintain consistent formatting
